The universal property of the equalizer E\xrightarrow {e}X of a
  diagram X\overset {f,g}{\rightrightarrows }Y is that, for any object Z equipped with
  a morphismZ\xrightarrow {d} X such that fd = gd, there exists a unique factorization Z\to  E of d: 




